SIMPLE: depolarize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Depolarize
<hw>De*po"lar*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Depolarized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Depolarizing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>de-</ets> + <ets>polarize</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧polarizer</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Opt.)</fld>
<def>To deprive of polarity; to reduce to an unpolarized
condition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This word has been inaccurately applied in optics to
describe the effect of a polarizing medium, as a crystalline plate, in
causing the reappearance of a ray, in consequence of a change in its
plane of polarization, which previously to the change was intercepted by
the analyzer.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>To free from polarization, as the
negative plate of the voltaic battery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Depolarizer</ent>⟦br⟧
